      "line": 598,
      "message": "Call home scenario is a TCP request from a pnf (netconf server) to the netconf client (SDNC), see 2. Solution overview\nhttps://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8071\n\nCallhome is not http(s)\n\nQ: is it possible to define ingress for TCP? As I understand this post:\nhttps://kubernetes.github.io/ingress-nginx/user-guide/exposing-tcp-udp-services/\nthis is not possible out of the box and needs additional configmaps and service definition.",
